; maize-14: mzdis round-trip fixture (AC6478, AC6483).
;
; Code-only, SECTION-clean (no SECTION directive at all -> everything lands in
; the default CODE region), no embedded DATA/STRING -- exactly the shape the
; spec's "Known limitation" section calls for so a purely linear sweep is exact
; by construction. Every instruction here uses a literal target/operand (never
; a label) so the assembled bytes are self-contained and don't depend on
; forward-reference resolution; nothing here is meant to actually run.
;
; Deliberately hits every addressing-mode family (regVal/immVal/regAddr/
; immAddr) and every operand-count shape (0/1/2/3, OUT's two-immediate shape,
; OUTR/IN's fixed-register-port shape, XCHG's fixed-two-register shape) named
; in AC6483. scripts/run-tests.ps1's mzdis_roundtrip test assembles this,
; disassembles the result with mzdis, reassembles mzdis's own output text, and
; diffs the two .mzb files byte-for-byte.

; ---- 0-operand ----
HALT
NOP
SETCRY
CLRCRY
SETINT
CLRINT
RET
IRET

; ---- 1-operand, plain register (CLR/INC/DEC/NOT/NEG/POP) ----
CLR R0
INC R1
DEC R2
NOT R3
NEG R3
POP R4

; ---- Jcc: immediate target only, all ten conditions (maize-64) ----
JZ $1234`5678
JNZ $12
JLT $1234
JB $12
JGT $12
JA $12
JGE $12
JLE $12
JBE $12
JAE $12

; ---- 1-operand, SrcFlagged, all four addressing modes (PUSH) ----
PUSH R5
PUSH $12
PUSH $1234

; ---- 1-operand, SrcFlagged, all four addressing modes (JMP family) ----
JMP R0
JMP $1234`5678
JMP @R1
JMP @$2000`0000

; ---- 2-operand, SrcFlagged + FixedReg, all four addressing modes (ALU family) ----
ADD R1 R0
ADD $05 R0
ADD @R1 R0
ADD @$3000`0000 R0

; ---- 2-operand, SrcFlagged + dereferenced FixedReg (ST/CMPIND/TSTIND) ----
ST R2 @R0
ST $05 @R0
CMPIND R1 @R0
CMPIND $01 @R0
TSTIND R1 @R0
TSTIND $01 @R0

; ---- CP / LD: same base opcode, mnemonic split by the srcAddr bit ----
CP $1234 R0
CP R1 R0
LD @R0 R2
LD @$5000`0000 R2

; ---- CPZ (regVal / immVal only, no address forms) ----
CPZ R1 R0
CPZ $05 R0

; ---- 3-operand, SrcFlagged + FixedReg + FixedReg (LEA/CMPXCHG/MULW/UMULW) ----
LEA R2 R0 R1
LEA $08 R0 R1
LEA @R2 R0 R1
LEA @$6000`0000 R0 R1
CMPXCHG R1 R2 R3
MULW R1 R2 R3
UMULW $02 R2 R3

; ---- OUT: SrcFlagged (op1) + PortImm (op2, always immediate) ----
; regVal and immVal only here: mazm's regimm_imm_compiler (OUT's compiler,
; src/mazm.cpp:1942) never checks operand1 for a leading '@', so out_regAddr_imm
; ($94) / out_immAddr_imm ($D4) are encodable (present in mzdis's decode table,
; matching README/maize_cpu.h) but are currently unreachable from mazm's own
; assembler syntax -- a pre-existing mazm gap unrelated to this card's scope,
; not something to route around here. regVal/immVal/regAddr/immAddr coverage
; for AC6483 comes from the ADD/CP-LD/JMP families above instead.
OUT R0 $0001
OUT $05 $0001

; ---- OUTR / IN: SrcFlagged + fixed register port ----
OUTR R0 R1
IN R1 R0

; ---- XCHG: fixed two-register shape ----
XCHG R0 R1

; ---- INT / SYS (SrcFlagged only, 2 rows) ----
INT R0
INT $01
SYS R0
SYS $01

; ---- Floating-point ISA (card maize-122) ----
; Arithmetic + FCMP: SrcFlagged op1 + FixedReg op2, all four addressing modes.
FADD R1.H0 R0.H0
FADD $40100000 R0.H0
FADD @R1 R0.H0
FADD @$3000`0000 R0.H0
FSUB R1.W0 R0.W0
FMUL R1.H0 R0.H0
FDIV R1.W0 R0.W0
FCMP R1.H0 R0.H0
FCMP $40100000 R0.H0
FCMP @R1 R0.H0
FCMP @$3000`0000 R0.H0
; FMA: SrcFlagged op1 + FixedReg op2 + FixedReg op3, all four addressing modes.
FMADD R0.H0 R1.H0 R2.H0
FMADD $3F800000 R1.H0 R2.H0
FMADD @R0 R1.H0 R2.H0
FMADD @$4000`0000 R1.H0 R2.H0
FMSUB R0.W0 R1.W0 R2.W0
; Register-only two-operand families (row-packed).
FSQRT R0.H0 R1.H0
FNEG R0.W0 R1.W0
FABS R0.H0 R1.H0
FMIN R0.H0 R1.H0
FMAX R0.W0 R1.W0
FCVTFF R0.H0 R1.W0
FCVTFS R0.H0 R1.B0
FCVTFU R0.W0 R1.Q0
FCVTSF R0.B0 R1.H0
FCVTUF R0.Q0 R1.W0
; FCSR access and the unordered predicate.
FGETCSR R5.B0
FSETCSR R5.B0
JP $12
SETP R0

HALT
